						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set-up in a field (situated) at the base of the hillock called Madagumalai.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Parakesarivarmaṉ Year 34: 941 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records that Śūṟan Nāgai, who is residing at Konṟaiyūr in Ollaiyūr-kūṟṟam made an image of Aiyyaṉ (Aiyyaṉār) and it (the image) was placed under the protection (of the mercantile body) <hi rend="italic">tigai āyiratt-aiññūṟṟuvar.</hi></p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Āvaṇam,</hi> issue No. 19. p. 62.</p>						

						</summary>
